race.comment: REINA ISABELLA (2) is a talented galloper who resumed further improved when dominating the 66 graders at Pakenham. Has a handy 3kg claim today and is sure to have come on. In a top barn and with average luck she should have these covered. JESSUP (7) won a 56 easily here and then was on pace again finding one too good at Kyneton. Has some weight relief and may form the quinella. SKY SISTA (4) has been jumped out since his close-up effort in a Ballarat 60. Has more to give and should be in the finish. CAPITAL GRACE (10) has been freshened since a plainer run at Geelong. Impressed winning a Maiden prior and on and would be in the mix. BLISTERING (6) has been racing in stronger and would be in the money if she put her best foot forward.
